<h1>Generate JWT using postman</h1>

Postman have a feature to genereate JWT without accessing in client side (Front-end) APP.

Follow these steps to generate access token (Oauth2):

<ul>
<li> go to 'Authorization' tab in request window</li>
<li> Select 'OAuth2' in Type (Security Type)</li>
<li> click on 'Generate New Access Token' </li>
<li> use`Grant Type` according to your scenario. In this case we will choose 'Password Credentials' </li>
<li> insert {Server IP}/auth/realms/{realm}/protocol/openid-connect/token' in Access token URL </li>
<li> Add Username and Password of any user of the selected realm to create its access token </li>
<li> Insert 'Cient ID' (name of your client) and request token </li>
